                        <li><strong>Not Financial or Energy Advice:</strong> The Service does not constitute financial, energy-trading, or professional advice. Your actual electricity tariff, taxes, grid fees, and final billing depend entirely on your specific energy provider (e.g., Tibber, aWATTar, Ostrom, or local utility companies).</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h2>3. Limitation of Liability</h2>
                    <p>In no event shall Logicpath Systems, nor its directors, employees, partners, agents, suppliers, or affiliates, be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, including without limitation, financial losses, unexpectedly high electricity bills, or loss of profits resulting from:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Your reliance on any data, prices, or recommendations (e.g., "best time to charge") displayed within the Service.</li>
                        <li>Your access to or use of, or inability to access or use, the Service.</li>
                        <li>Any unauthorized access, use, or alteration of your transmissions or content.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>You agree that you use the Service and make decisions regarding your energy consumption at your own risk.</p>

                    <h2>4. Third-Party Links</h2>
                    <p>Our Service may contain links to third-party web sites or services (e.g., referral links to energy providers) that are not owned or controlled by Logicpath Systems.</p> 
                    <p>Logicpath Systems has no control over, and assumes no responsibility for, the content, privacy policies, or practices of any third-party websites or services. You acknowledge and agree that Logicpath Systems shall not be responsible or liable, directly or indirectly, for any damage or loss caused or alleged to be caused by or in connection with the use of or reliance on any such content, goods, or services available on or through any such websites or services.</p>

